cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.DM, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with the problem of computing a multiway join in MapReduce, which is a common task in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses optimization on communication cost, which involves data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The use of MapReduce also involves distributed computing, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions the identification of Heavy Hitters, which is a common problem in data mining and falls under cs.DM (Data Mining). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and experimentation of the algorithm, which involves machine learning and statistical analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category as well.
